    "body": "### Problem\n\n<C-l>-default does not clear previous search results with ui2, previous search result persist during subsequent keystrokes (e.g., hjkl). (state \n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\necho 'a ab abc' > repro.txt && nvim --clean -c \"lua require('vim._core.ui2').enable({enable=true})\" repro.txt\n\n1. search char 'a':  /a\n2. clear search results: <C-l> (search result is cleared)\n3. move curosr: h or l (previous search result reappears in cmdline)\n4. manually type `:nohlsearch`: search result cleared and does not persist on cursor movements\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nno search result in the cmdline\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-221+g39410ef42b\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nna\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nwsl2 ubuntu 22.04\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwindows-terminal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
